I"í<p>Sourdough French toast is the perfect combo of sweet and sour. It is a great way to use day old bread and a quick breakfast!</p>

<h1 id="step-by-step-instructions">Step by Step Instructions</h1>

<h3 id="1-mix">1. Mix</h3>

<p>Measure and mix 3/4 cup milk, 1 1/2 tsp vanilla, 1 egg, and 3/4 tsp cinnamon in a bowl.</p>

<p><img src="/images/french_mix.jpg" alt="Mix" /></p>

<h3 id="2-cut-bread">2. Cut Bread</h3>

<p>Cut bread into 4 slices, each 1/2 inch thick.</p>

<p><img src="/images/french_slice.jpg" alt="Bread" /></p>

<h3 id="3-heat-pan">3. Heat Pan.</h3>

<p>Heat pan on medium. Once hot add butter and let dissolve.</p>

<h3 id="4-soak">4. Soak.</h3>

<p>Take a slice of bread and dunk it into the bowl. Flip the bread and submerge the other side. Place the soaked bread into pan. Repeat with three other slices.</p>

